    <h1>N. KOREAN LEADER&#x2019;S LET&#xAD;TERS TO U.S. PRES&#xAD;I&#xAD;DENT DON&#xAD;ALD TRUMP RE&#xAD;VEALED</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200917/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-17"><time>2020-09-17</time></a>
        - <span>WORLD</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Like the brief time we had to­gether a year ago in Sin­ga­pore, ev­ery minute we shared 103 days ago in Hanoi was also a mo­ment of glory that re­mains a pre­cious mem­ory. Such a pre­cious mem­ory that I have in my un­wa­ver­ing re­spect for you will pro­vide an im­pe­tus for me to take my steps when we walk towards each other again some day in the fu­ture. I also be­lieve that the deep and spe­cial friend­ship be­tween us will work as a mag­i­cal force…</p>
    <p>I be­lieve the one day will come sooner or later when we sit down to­gether to make great things hap­pen, with the will to give an­other chance to our mu­tual trust. Such a day should come again. It may well be recorded as yet an­other fan­tas­tic mo­ment in his­tory.</p>
    <p>July 6 MR KIM</p>

